        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer983144469" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18139004345371134590">This book was fascinating. The talk of how psychiatry came to be and why it began labeling anyone who heard voices as &quot;mentally ill&quot; was very interesting-and scary. While I did really enjoy all the historical evidence of people who heard voices and were not &quot;sick&quot; in any way-especially Socrates-I wish the book had gone into more modern examples, perhaps talked about some other cultures outside the Western Hemisphere that often believe voice-hearing to be a normal thing. </span>
  <span id="freeText18139004345371134590" style="display:none">This book was fascinating. The talk of how psychiatry came to be and why it began labeling anyone who heard voices as "mentally ill" was very interesting-and scary. While I did really enjoy all the historical evidence of people who heard voices and were not "sick" in any way-especially Socrates-I wish the book had gone into more modern examples, perhaps talked about some other cultures outside the Western Hemisphere that often believe voice-hearing to be a normal thing. </span>
