        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer192073175" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13928728407058039130">Not as audacious as Jaynes&apos; theories on the subject, this book&apos;s still a good read, which want us to try to adopt a non (or less) conformist point of view about people who hear voices. The phenomenon may be a plague in a lot of cases, but it seems there&apos;s also many people that copes well with it. Some paragraphs seem a little superfluous (the one describing a personal experience in an isolation tank doesn&apos;t really seem to demonstrate anything), others, as the one about the history of pathologiza</span>
  <span id="freeText13928728407058039130" style="display:none">Not as audacious as Jaynes' theories on the subject, this book's still a good read, which want us to try to adopt a non (or less) conformist point of view about people who hear voices. The phenomenon may be a plague in a lot of cases, but it seems there's also many people that copes well with it. Some paragraphs seem a little superfluous (the one describing a personal experience in an isolation tank doesn't really seem to demonstrate anything), others, as the one about the history of pathologization, are really interesting.</span>
